&lt;p&gt;Oldham’s new and innovative Digital Hub is striving to make a real difference to the health and wellbeing of the Oldham community and you could be a key part in driving the service forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;gtd is recruiting to a number of urgent primary care ACP roles, which have arisen within the Digital Hub. The role is deemed a key asset in ensuring patients are seen as quickly and safely as possible, in the right place and at the right time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Based at the Integrated Care Centre, you will have a unique opportunity to work within a  service that will contribute towards transforming how the Oldham population accesses&lt;br /&gt;healthcare. Furthermore, you will have a key role within the Digital Hub’s multidisciplinary team to support the Urgent and Emergency Care by Appointment Agenda.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an excellent prospect to work alongside a team who has a real commitment to continuous improvement, shared learning and best practice, while being passionate about providing Oldham patients with the highest possible quality care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A full advert containing lots of further detail is attached along with a job description for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
